Raymond ARCINIEGA, Petitioner-Appellant, v. Edward R. FREEMAN, U. S. Marshal, Respondent-Appellee. No. 26244. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 30, 1971.

Before CARTER, WRIGHT and TRASK, Circuit Judges.

Pursuant to the order of the Supreme Court of the United States, dated October 26, 1971, 404 U.S. 4, 92 S.Ct. 22, 30 L.Ed.2d 126 reversing 439 F.2d 776, this cause is remanded to the district court for further proceedings.
